{
  "id": "019d24a3-7709-7a02-91ad-e30866bae9c3",
  "content": "## Session Watcher (inotify) — v0.4.5\n\nServer-side file watcher that monitors ~/.claude/sessions/*.jsonl for real-time dashboard visibility into active Claude Code sessions.\n\n### Architecture\n- Module: crates/corvia-server/src/dashboard/session_watcher.rs\n- Uses notify crate v7 (inotify on Linux, polling fallback)\n- Incremental JSONL parser: seeks to last offset, reads new complete lines\n- In-memory HashMap with 500-session cap\n- 200ms event debouncing to batch rapid writes\n- broadcast::Sender for SSE push updates\n\n### Endpoints\n- GET /api/dashboard/sessions/hook — REST snapshot of active sessions\n- GET /api/dashboard/sessions/hook/stream — SSE with initial snapshot + real-time deltas\n\n### HookSession Fields\nsession_id, state (Active/Stale/Ended), workspace, git_branch, agent_type, parent_session_id, corvia_agent_id, started_at, last_activity, duration_secs, turn_count, tool_calls, active_tool, tools_used\n\n### Safety Mitigations (from quad-review)\n- Partial-line safety: offset tracks last newline, not file length\n- Symlink rejection before reading any file\n- 1MB max line size, 500 max sessions\n- No prompt preview (security: avoids leaking secrets)\n- Broadcast lag recovery sends fresh snapshot\n- Graceful degradation: inotify failure falls back to 2s polling\n\n### Stale Detection\n- Active with no events for 10min marked Stale\n- Ended or no events for 60min evicted from map\n- Sweep runs every 30s\n\n### Event Types Parsed\nsession_start, user_prompt, tool_start, tool_end, session_end (v:1 schema). Unknown types silently ignored for forward compat.\n\n### Tests: 16 unit tests covering event application, incremental reads, partial lines, invalid JSON, stale detection, max sessions limit, symlink rejection.",
